# R1 stage0-mes byte-identity pins.  Checked by `/usr/bin/sha256sum -c mes.answers`
# (kaem aborts HARD on a non-zero return -> build fails).  These 13 values are the
# CANONICAL upstream checksums from live-bootstrap steps/mes-0.27.1/mes-0.27.1.amd64.checksums
# (read verbatim 2026-06-20).  Live-bootstrap publishes paths under /usr/...; we install to
# the staging root DESTDIR=/build/output, so the gate paths are /build/output/usr/... .
#
# PINNABLE NOW (high confidence): mes-m2 is produced by M2-Planet/M1/hex2/blood-elf (R0,
# byte-gated against amd64.answers) from the sha-pinned mes source, so it should reproduce
# bit-for-bit.  The libc .a/.s and mescc.scm are produced by mes-m2 + MesCC and depend on the
# baked prefix string being /usr (see mes.kaem: @prefix@ -> /usr, NOT the staging path) and on
# the relative-path mescc invocations matching live-bootstrap.  If the first cloud build
# mismatches, the divergence is environmental (prefix string, M2libc copy, tool determinism),
# NOT a trust hole — re-pin from the green build and investigate.  mes-m2 mismatching WOULD be
# a real R0 reproduction problem.
